From 2e4289180622d9430973df309bd829848e4a7a73 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Paul E. McKenney" <paulmck@kernel.org>
Date: Tue, 22 Jun 2021 11:57:15 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] rcu-tasks: Fix synchronize_rcu_rude() typo in comment

References: bnc#1189998 (PREEMPT_RT prerequisite backports)
Patch-mainline: v5.15-rc1
Git-commit: e4be1f44b6f8d36a8607a598d41c766044b74be3

This commit replaces the fictitious synchronize_rcu_rude() function with
its real-world synchronize_rcu_tasks_rude() counterpart.

Signed-off-by: Paul E. McKenney <paulmck@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Mel Gorman <mgorman@suse.de>
---
 kernel/rcu/tasks.h | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/rcu/tasks.h b/kernel/rcu/tasks.h
index 1faf7937e242..6591914af486 100644
--- a/kernel/rcu/tasks.h
+++ b/kernel/rcu/tasks.h
@@ -642,8 +642,8 @@ void exit_tasks_rcu_finish(void) { exit_tasks_rcu_finish_trace(current); }
 //
 // "Rude" variant of Tasks RCU, inspired by Steve Rostedt's trick of
 // passing an empty function to schedule_on_each_cpu().  This approach
-// provides an asynchronous call_rcu_tasks_rude() API and batching
-// of concurrent calls to the synchronous synchronize_rcu_rude() API.
+// provides an asynchronous call_rcu_tasks_rude() API and batching of
+// concurrent calls to the synchronous synchronize_rcu_tasks_rude() API.
 // This invokes schedule_on_each_cpu() in order to send IPIs far and wide
 // and induces otherwise unnecessary context switches on all online CPUs,
 // whether idle or not.
